--------------Database Design---------------------

It is an organizing of data according to database model.

Database designer must determine:
a.) What data to be stored ?
b.) How data elememts interrelate with each other?

It involves the classifying data and identifying relationship.

Relationship Understanding
a.) One-to-One
b.) One-to-Many
c.) Many-to-Many

Practical Implementation - School database:

Tables Created with Dummy Data

a.) classes
c.) sections
d.) students
e.) subjects
f.) subject_teachers
g.) teachers
h.) department

